dismissalText.commentary: Hamilton Masakadza c Chandimal b Kulasekara 4 (23b 0x4 0x6 21m) SR: 17.39

dismissalComment.html: This was coming. Kulasekara has been harassing Hamilton with his two-card trick. In and out. Out and in. This one shapes away from short of length, Hamilton had stepped out, trying to counter the swing, but this one kicks up and cuts away. He had a poke at it and the ball took the outside edge. Gone!

dismissalText.commentary: Upul Tharanga run out (Cremer/Taibu) 72 (79b 8x4 1x6 110m) SR: 91.13

dismissalComment.html: Dear o dear .. what have they done? Tharanga is run out He sacrificed for his captain. It was pushed to short third man and DIlshan runs across. Tharanga stops after couple of steps but Dilshan keeps running. And Tharanga decides to sacrifice himself and crosses over. Hmmm. Dilshan seems to angry with himself.

commentTextItems.html: Cremer tries to surpris DIlshan with a bouncer, yes a bouncer!, and Dilshan responds with a pull to fine-leg boundary! Congrats Sri Lanka.They win by 9 wickets. Comprehensive. Wonderful tournament for Dilshan who has got back to form in style. A fine tournament for Zimbabwe as well.

commentPostTextItems.html: This is Umpire Rudi's last ODI. Rudi takes a stump as a souvenir. He is congratulated by Zimbabwe and the Sri Lankan players.
Thilan: "Completing 4500 runs with a century ... well done Dilshan ...."
Please hang for quotes from post-match ceremony.

Elton Chigumbura "Sri Lanka bowled well and put us under pressure from ball one. There are lots of positives to get out of this tournament. Especially our batsmen. Unfortunately we are having a break after this. But it's good for the next season. Hopefully we are going in the right way and we will keep winning more matches. Keep watching us and keep supporting us."

Man of the series is Brendan Taylor: "It;s very satisfying to get where we are. Unfortuanately we didn't back it up in the final but we are pleased with how we have gone. Not just my self, others have done welll. Taibu, masakadza and spinners. I am probably more relaxed in this series. Opening is new to me. I haven't done it for a while. It 's nice to play with a good bunch of people."

Dilshan: "I am very happy. the boys performed well. The two fast bowlers set the tone for us by bowling really well. We brought lots of youngsters here and they have got opportunities and done well. Chandimal got a hundred and Jeevan Mendis is a good allrounder .. we are looking at World Cup. I got my form back as well. I want to carry it to the World Cup. I would like to thank my team-mates for supporting me as a captain. It wasn't easy to captain and I have enjoyed it. I like a challenge. "
Dilshan accepts the Trophy and poses together with his team. Happy scenes.
That's it from us. Thanks for logging on. Good bye and good luck

commentTextItems.html: turns outside off and Dilshan cuts for couple of runs
leans forward to caress it through the off side. the scores are level
short in length and it has been pulled away
drops it slightly short and Dilshan retains the strike with a cut shot

headshotImage.longCaption: Dinesh Chandimal, player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: wide down the leg side. Just six more now
quicker, Dilshan tries to swing it over square-leg but misses . the ball rolls of the pad
Dilshan's seventh ODI ton and his first against ZImbabwe. First as a captain of course. It was slightly short in length and Dilshan went back to cut it to backward point boundary
turns in from outside off, squeezed to square-leg
a long hop arrives and Chandimal pulls it to the boundary

commentPreTextItems.html: Lasith malinga time again: "Who is the best singer in the dressing room?
Tell us about something unusual you recently did that you enjoyed?
When I was playing county cricket last time in England, I drove from London to Kent at 240kph - definitely better than bowling a 100mph fast one! "

dismissalText.commentary: Brendan Taylor c Samaraweera b Fernando 19 (22b 3x4 0x6 45m) SR: 86.36

dismissalComment.html: What a stunner from Samaraweera at Gully. It was a short of length delivery outside off and Taylor just opened his bat-face and tried to guide it to third man. The ball flew low to right of Samaraweera who swooped forward to take it inches of the turf. And boy is he delirious or what?! Big wicket this.

dismissalText.commentary: Craig Ervine run out (Kapugedera/Mathews) 9 (24b 1x4 0x6 34m) SR: 37.5

dismissalComment.html: Ervine is run out It was pushed towards backward point and there is confusion between the two over the single. Taibu takes couple of steps down the track and Ervine rushes half-way. Taibu stops and turns. too late for Ervine who is unable to beat the throw which comes in to Angelo who breaks the stumps

dismissalText.commentary: Tatenda Taibu c Kapugedera b Fernando 71 (93b 4x4 0x6 125m) SR: 76.34

dismissalComment.html: Almost like Taylor. Weak shot. It was a short delivery outside off and Taibu almost guided it straight, tapped it straight, to backward point. What a soft dismissal. What a fine knock, though. He led Zimbabwe's revival

headshotImage.longCaption: Ajantha Mendis player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Elton Chigumbura c Dilshan b BAW Mendis 10 (18b 0x4 0x6 14m) SR: 55.55

dismissalComment.html: Tickets please here! Mendis flicks it full on a length and Elton chips it tamely to covers. And Zimbabwe continue to wobble

dismissalText.commentary: Greg Lamb b BMAJ Mendis 37 (65b 1x4 0x6 86m) SR: 56.92

dismissalComment.html: Clatter! Jeevan has nailed Lamb. It landed on the middle stump line and turned. Lamb went for the big slog sweep but no wood on leather. It was leather on the wood. Gone!

dismissalText.commentary: Charles Coventry c Tharanga b BMAJ Mendis 18 (12b 3x4 0x6 11m) SR: 150

dismissalComment.html: But he is gone now! Again looking to be aggressive, he went down the track and heaved it straight to long-on! 200 looks a long way from here

dismissalText.commentary: Graeme Cremer b Fernando 5 (10b 0x4 0x6 16m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: The death rattle! Full in length, fast, and tilts in to move past the waft, hits the pad and clips the stumps!

dismissalComment.html: And he is gone now. Full delivery on the middle, the googly this time, Price shovels it straight to short midwicket. And then they were one.

dismissalText.commentary: Chris Mpofu run out (Dilshan/Chandimal) 6 (9b 0x4 0x6 9m) SR: 66.66

dismissalComment.html: They don't get to 200. It was pushed to right of short midwicket and they go for the run. Dilshan swoops in, fires a low through to Chandimal who breaks the stumps

dismissalText.commentary: Upul Tharanga run out (Cremer/Taibu) 72 (79b 8x4 1x6 110m) SR: 91.13

dismissalComment.html: Dear o dear .. what have they done? Tharanga is run out He sacrificed for his captain. It was pushed to short third man and DIlshan runs across. Tharanga stops after couple of steps but Dilshan keeps running. And Tharanga decides to sacrifice himself and crosses over. Hmmm. Dilshan seems to angry with himself.
